<template><div><h1 id="guide-to-town-of-host-enhanced-tohedata" tabindex="-1"><a class="header-anchor" href="#guide-to-town-of-host-enhanced-tohedata"><span><font color=#f0b6d5>Guide to Town of Host: Enhanced - <font color=#aaed3d>TOHEData</font></font></span></a></h1>
<p>TOHE-Data is a folder that holds important lists, as well as some customization features.
In the root directory of your mod folder (<code v-pre>...\Among Us\TOHE-DATA\</code>) you'll see a few files.</p>
<h4 id="banlist-txt" tabindex="-1"><a class="header-anchor" href="#banlist-txt"><span><font color=#aaed3d>BanList.txt</font></span></a></h4>
<p><code v-pre>BanList.txt</code> is a list of friendcodes that will be unable to join your lobby.</p>
<h4 id="denyname-txt" tabindex="-1"><a class="header-anchor" href="#denyname-txt"><span><font color=#aaed3d>DenyName.txt</font></span></a></h4>
<p><code v-pre>DenyName.txt</code> is a list of names that will be filtered out of the game.</p>
<h4 id="whitelist-txt" tabindex="-1"><a class="header-anchor" href="#whitelist-txt"><span><font color=#aaed3d>WhiteList.txt</font></span></a></h4>
<p><code v-pre>WhiteList.txt</code> is a list of friend-codes that will be exempt from blacklisted platforms, along with level requirements.</p>
<h4 id="default-teamplate-txt" tabindex="-1"><a class="header-anchor" href="#default-teamplate-txt"><span><font color=#aaed3d>Default_Teamplate.txt</font></span></a></h4>
<p><code v-pre>Default_Teamplate.txt</code> is the Default TOHE Template file. If you wish to reset your templates to default, You can use this. (No idea why it says Teamplate.)</p>
<h4 id="moderators-txt" tabindex="-1"><a class="header-anchor" href="#moderators-txt"><span><font color=#aaed3d>Moderators.txt</font></span></a></h4>
<p><code v-pre>Moderators.txt</code> is a list of friend-codes that will receive a nice Moderator tag as well as permissions to moderate your lobby. Only grant users you trust these permissions! (This will be covered on the Tags Guide page.)<br>
Note: While this system does work, there is a new/easier system to give out Tags/Permissions</p>
<h4 id="vip-list-txt" tabindex="-1"><a class="header-anchor" href="#vip-list-txt"><span><font color=#aaed3d>VIP-List.txt</font></span></a></h4>
<p><code v-pre>VIP-List.txt</code> is a list of friend-codes that will be given a sweet VIP tag as well as permissions to change their name color. (This will be covered on the Tags Guide page.)<br>
Note: While this system does work, there is a new/easier system to give out Tags/Permissions</p>
<h4 id="template-txt" tabindex="-1"><a class="header-anchor" href="#template-txt"><span><font color=#aaed3d>template.txt</font></span></a></h4>
<p><code v-pre>template.txt</code> is a list that houses the <code v-pre>welcome</code> and <code v-pre>onMeeting</code> templates. You can also add custom templates here as well. (This will be covered on the Templates Guide page.)</p>
<h4 id="language-folder" tabindex="-1"><a class="header-anchor" href="#language-folder"><span><font color=#aaed3d>Language Folder</font></span></a></h4>
<p>The <code v-pre>Language</code> Folder holds <code v-pre>template.dat</code>, as well as <code v-pre>templateRoleColor.dat</code>! <code v-pre>template.dat</code> allows you to edit the names of almost everything! <code v-pre>templateRoleColor.dat</code> allows you to change the colors that roles use.</p>
<h4 id="savedata-folder" tabindex="-1"><a class="header-anchor" href="#savedata-folder"><span><font color=#aaed3d>SaveData Folder</font></span></a></h4>
<p>The <code v-pre>SaveData</code> Folder holds your <code v-pre>Options.json</code>. This houses your TOHE Settings, and is where you find/add Presets.</p>
<h4 id="tags-folder" tabindex="-1"><a class="header-anchor" href="#tags-folder"><span><font color=#aaed3d>Tags Folder</font></span></a></h4>
<p>The <code v-pre>Tags</code> Folder holds everything relating to Tags, more on this covered on the Tags page.</p>
<p>You can visit <RouteLink to="/Resources.html">Resources</RouteLink> to view Variables, Text Formatting Tags, Usable Fonts/Symbols, &amp; more that will assist you in customizing your <b><i>best</i></b> lobbies!</p>
<h3 id="now-that-you-ve-seen-tohe-data-let-s-start-setting-up-some-templates" tabindex="-1"><a class="header-anchor" href="#now-that-you-ve-seen-tohe-data-let-s-start-setting-up-some-templates"><span>Now that you've seen TOHE-Data, let's start setting up some Templates!</span></a></h3>
</div></template>


